HEADWORD: Opisthodome
<hw>O*pis"tho*dome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>opisthodomus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <grk>'o`pisqen</grk> behind +
<grk>do`mos</grk> house: cf. F. <ets>opisthodome</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A back chamber; especially, that part of the
naos, or cella, farthest from the main entrance, sometimes having an
entrance of its own, and often used as a treasury.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opisthoglypha</ent>⟦br⟧
